## Verification Plan

### Automated / Self-Test
- Start both server and client (`npm run dev` in each folder)
- Test Near Me: click button, allow location, verify API call includes `lat/lng/radiusKm`
- Test lobby chat: join lobby as two users, send messages, verify persistence after lobby COMPLETED
- Test history page: filter by sport, status, role — verify results change
- Test profile: add bio/skill level, save, view as another user

### Manual Checklist
- [ ] After a lobby ends (status → COMPLETED), chat tab still shows all messages
- [ ] "Near Me" shows lobbies within selected radius
- [ ] `/history` page loads with all filters working
- [ ] Profile completeness bar disappears once all fields filled
- [ ] Past matches tab on Feed shows only COMPLETED lobbies

---

## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q1 — Lobby Group Chat Access:** Should the lobby chat be visible to **all confirmed players only**, or also to **pending/waitlisted players**? Or completely **public** (anyone who can see the lobby)?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q2 — Near Me radius default:** What default radius should "Near Me" use? Suggested: **10 km** default with options 5 / 10 / 25 / 50 km.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q3 — Match History page — private vs public:** Should `/history/:userId` for another user be accessible to anyone logged in, or only to the user themselves?

> [!NOTE]
> **Q4 — Profile location field:** Should this be a free-text field (e.g. "Islamabad, Pakistan") or use the same Pakistan city dropdown?

> [!NOTE]
> **Q5 — Past matches in Feed:** Should past matches only show YOUR lobbies, or everyone's completed lobbies (community-wide)?
